'''''Tourist Train''''' (Italian: '''''Treno popolare''''') is a 1933 Italian [[comedy film]] directed by [[Raffaello Matarazzo]] and starring [[Marcello Spada]], [[Lina Gennari]] and [[Carlo Petrangeli]]. The film portrays the comic adventures of a group of summertime travellers. It was shot on the [[Florence-Rome railway]] and in [[Orvieto]]. It was one of a number of films made during the 1930s whose [[Realism (arts)|realism]] pointed in the direction of the later development of [[Italian neorealism]].<ref>Brunetta p.101</ref>

